race.comment: BACK ME UP BENNY (6) is racing in great heart this campaign and looks a winning chance here. He looked the winner but was just out-gunned late. Holder sticks and the map looks similar for him. He can fight out the finish. WHATSANAMEGEORGE (4) brings the Guru Warrior form which looks better and better. He's a previous track and distance winner who might be able to settle closer. He looks a danger. Victorian galloper THE MUFFIN MAN (1) makes the trip across the border and might be ready to peak third-up to 1950m. He can run a big race for Pannell from the inside draw. ALAINGE (9) is an each-way chance on her best form, while THINKINGNINTYNINE (10) can roll forward and stick on. He is worth some thought for the minor money.
